people’s spirit, resourcefulness, self-sufficiency, and their persistence in the struggle against nature’s immense power. The 1950 event changed the way these fires are fought in Alberta and elsewhere. The Chinchaga Firestorm will appeal to wildland fire scientists, foresters, forest ecologists and policy makers, as well as those who are interested in western Canadian history and ecology.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aFeux de frichesxAlbertaxChinchaga, Rivière. 0aFeux de frichesxAspect de l'environnement. 0aFire ecologyxAlbertaxChinchaga River. 0aFire ecologyzAlbertazChinchaga River. 0aFire ecologyzCanadaxHistory. 0aForest firesxAlbertaxChinchaga River. 0aForest firesxEnvironmental aspectszCanadaxHistory. 0aForest firesxEnvironmental aspects. 0aForest firesxPrevention and control. 0aForest fireszAlbertazChinchaga River. 0aForêtsxIncendiesxAlbertaxChinchaga, Rivière. 0aForêtsxIncendiesxAspect de l'environnement. 0aForêtsxIncendiesxPrévention et maîtrisexAlbertaxChinchaga River. 0aFuméexAspect de l'environnement. 0aSmokexEnvironmental aspects. 0aWildfiresxAlbertaxChinchaga River. 0aWildfiresxEnvironmental aspects. 0aWildfireszAlbertazChinchaga River. 0aÉcologie des feuxxAlbertaxChinchaga, Rivière. 7aNATURE / Ecology.2bisacsh  aEnvironment.  aForestry.  aWildfire.1 aFlannigan, Mike, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2015z978311127402708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2015z978311127703540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978177212015840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781772120158423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781772120158/original  a978-3-11-127402-7  ACUP Complete 